    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\n`vim.pack.update()` can show pending plugin updates interactively, but there does not seem to be a supported Lua API to query them programmatically.\n\nA machine-readable API for pending updates would enable things like:\n\n- statusline update counters\n- dashboard widgets\n- notifications\n- custom commands showing available plugin updates\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nExpose pending updates in a machine-readable form.\n\nFor example, one of these would solve it:\n- `vim.pack.update(..., { check = true })`\n- `vim.pack.check()`\n- `vim.pack.outdated()`\n\nExample:\n```lua\nlocal updates = vim.pack.outdated()\nprint(vim.inspect(updates))\nprint(#updates)\n```\n\nExpected output:\n```\n{\n  { name = \"fzf-lua\", current = \"abc123\", target = \"def456\" },\n  { name = \"plenary.nvim\", current = \"111111\", target = \"222222\" },\n}\n2\n```",
