        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "I am not particularly confident that this is a high demand functionality. The big downside of adding this is that it will lock and limit implementation of actual updating. For instance, the structure of `details` would have to be established and changing it would be a breaking change.\n\nOn the other hand, adding this can follow a more or less established pattern of \"dry run\". Maybe if done even more minimal than in the diff, it can be doable. Like:\n- Add `opts.dryrun = false|true` or `opts.dry`. Note: a slight problem is that it conflicts with `opts.force`.\n- If it is dry run, return (before writing a lock file) only `{ name = p.spec.name, rev = p.info.sha_head, target = p.infi.sha_target }`. A `path` can be taken from `vim.pack.get()` and `details` can be computed by potential users via `vim.system()` as they please.\n\nBut in any case, I think it requires an extra care with the intention and API. For example:\n- I am not sure how to handle progress in this case: should it be shown or not?\n- Maybe a better place is `vim.pack.get()` with something like `opts.fetch` that will fetch updates and add `target` field to the output?",
