            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "I think enhancing `vim.pack.get()` makes the most sense here. This keeps it the main \"get information about the plugins\" function while not adding return value for `vim.pack.update()`. Something like this looks reasonable:\n- Add `rev_target` field to the return value that represent the revision to which `spec.version` points. I.e. this is the revision that will be applied after accepting `vim.pack.update()`.\n- Add `opts.offline = false|true` (with `false` being default) that has the same meaning as in `vim.pack.update()`. The small annoyance is the different default value, but reusing the name if it has the same meaning seems appropriate.\n\nI hope to take a look at this within couple of weeks.",
